-- Software stocks drag Indian shares to 2-1/2 week closing low
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Wed Apr 16, 2014 06:06AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, April 16 (Reuters) - Indian shares fell on Wednesday to mark their lowest close in 2-1/2 weeks as software stocks slumped on caution ahead of India's top IT services provider Tata Consultancy Services' <TCS.NS> quarterly results later in the day.

TCS provisionally fell 2.9 percent, Wipro <WIPR.NS> lost 2.7 percent while Infosys Ltd <INFY.NS> slumped 3 percent.